===亞裔美國人===
{{main|亞裔美國人}}
儘管早在[[美國獨立戰爭|美國獨立戰爭]]之前就有亞裔生活在北美殖民地，<ref>{{cite web |url=https://jacl.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2006_GoldMountain_CurGuide.pdf |title=The Journey from Gold Mountain: The Asian American Experience |publisher=Japanese American Citizens League |page=3 |date=2006 |access-date=2016-11-27 |archive-date=2019-04-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412033038/https://jacl.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2006_GoldMountain_CurGuide.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=California Declares Filipino American History Month |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/stories/2009/09/07/daily59.html |newspaper=San Francisco Business Times |date=2009-09-10 |access-date=2011-02-14 |archive-date=2021-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211112054427/https://www.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/stories/2009/09/07/daily59.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>但大部分亞裔是從19世紀中後期開始才移民至美國的。<ref name="AAWA2009">{{cite web |url=http://www.capaa.wa.gov/documents/AchievementGapReport.pdf |title=Asian Americans in Washington State: Closing Their Hidden Achievement Gaps |first1=Shirley |last1=Hune |first2=David T. |last2=Takeuchi |first3=Third |last3=Andresen |first4=Seunghye |last4=Hong |first5=Julie |last5=Kang |first6=Mavae'Aho |last6=Redmond |first7=Jeomja |last7=Yeo |date=April 2009 |work=Commission on Asian Pacific American Affairs |publisher=State of Washington |access-date=2012-02-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101103144615/http://www.capaa.wa.gov/documents/AchievementGapReport.pdf |archive-date=2010-11-03 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>2010年，美國有1730萬亞裔，佔總人口的5.6%。<ref name="2010 Census AA">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/prod/cen2010/briefs/c2010br-02.pdf|title=2010 United States Census statistics|access-date=2021-09-09|archive-date=2011-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110429214029/http://www.census.gov/prod/cen2010/briefs/c2010br-02.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=b02001>{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |title=B02001. RACE – Universe: TOTAL POPULATION |work=2008 American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates |access-date=2010-02-28 |publisher=[[美国普查局|美国普查局]] |archive-date=1996-12-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/19961227012639/https://www.census.gov/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>亞裔最多的州是加利福尼亞州，共有560萬。<ref name="FFFCENSUS2011" />佔比最高的州是夏威夷州，佔比57%。<ref name="FFFCENSUS2011">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov/newsroom/releases/archives/facts_for_features_special_editions/cb11-ff06.html |title=Asian/Pacific American Heritage Month: May 2011 |date=2011-12-07 |work=Facts for Features |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau |access-date=2012-01-04 |archive-date=2012-09-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120908054957/http://www.census.gov/newsroom/releases/archives/facts_for_features_special_editions/cb11-ff06.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>城市人口在亞裔當中佔比很高，[[大洛杉矶地区|大洛杉矶地区]]、[[紐約都會區|紐約都會區]]和[[舊金山灣區|舊金山灣區]]有大量亞裔。<ref>{{cite news |title=Asian Americans had higher poverty rate than whites in 2011, study says |author=Shan Li |url=http://www.latimes.com/business/money/la-fi-mo-asian-american-poverty-20130502,0,7842601.story |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=2013-05-03 |access-date=2013-05-06 |quote=In 2011, for example, nearly a third of Asians in the U.S. lived in the metropolitan regions around Los Angeles, San Francisco and New York. |archive-date=2013-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130506045430/http://www.latimes.com/business/money/la-fi-mo-asian-american-poverty-20130502,0,7842601.story |dead-url=no }}<br />{{cite web |title=Selected Population Profile in the United States |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/IPTable?_bm=y&-context=ip&-reg=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201:031;ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201PR:031;ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201T:031;ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201TPR:031&-qr_name=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201&-qr_name=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201PR&-qr_name=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201T&-qr_name=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201TPR&-ds_name=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_&-tree_id=3307&-geo_id=31000US16980&-geo_id=31000US19100&-geo_id=31000US31100&-geo_id=31000US35620&-geo_id=31000US41740&-geo_id=31000US41860&-search_results=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en |work=U.S. Census |publisher=U.S. Department of Commerce |access-date=2011-06-25 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212041712/http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/IPTable?_bm=y&-context=ip&-reg=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201:031;ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201PR:031;ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201T:031;ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201TPR:031&-qr_name=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201&-qr_name=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201PR&-qr_name=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201T&-qr_name=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_S0201TPR&-ds_name=ACS_2007_3YR_G00_&-tree_id=3307&-geo_id=31000US16980&-geo_id=31000US19100&-geo_id=31000US31100&-geo_id=31000US35620&-geo_id=31000US41740&-geo_id=31000US41860&-search_results=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en |archive-date=2020-02-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

亞裔不是單一的族群，而是由許多國家的移民及其後裔組成的。包括中國、台灣、日本、韓國、印度、巴基斯坦、菲律賓、越南、柬埔寨、寮國等。亞裔的收入和教育水平高於其他種族，而這一差距還在持續擴大。<ref>{{cite book|author1=Meizhu Lui |author2=Barbara Robles |author3=Betsy Leondar-Wright |author4=Rose Brewer |author5={{link-en|Rebecca Adamson|Rebecca Adamson}}|title=The Color of Wealth |year=2006|publisher=The New Press }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/prod/2004pubs/p20-550.pdf|title=US Census Bureau report on educational attainment in the United States, 2003|access-date=2006-07-31|archive-date=2021-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211002152600/https://www.census.gov/prod/2004pubs/p20-550.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal| date =February 2007| title =The American Community-Asians: 2004| publisher =U.S. Census Bureau| url =https://www.census.gov/prod/2007pubs/acs-05.pdf| access-date =2007-09-05| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20070926002242/http://www.census.gov/prod/2007pubs/acs-05.pdf| archive-date =2007-09-26| url-status =dead}}</ref>

亞裔被稱為「[[模範少數族裔|模範少數族裔]]」<ref>{{cite book |title=The myth of the model minority: Asian Americans facing racism |last=Chou |first=Rosalind |author2=Joe R. Feagin |year=2008 |publisher=Paradigm Publishers |isbn=978-1-59451-586-6 |page=x |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_HoaAQAAIAAJ&q=Model+Minority+Asians |access-date=2011-02-09 |archive-date=2021-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211112053146/https://books.google.com/books?id=_HoaAQAAIAAJ&q=Model+Minority+Asians |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Report Takes Aim at 'Model Minority' Stereotype of Asian-American Students |author=Tamar Lewin |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/06/10/education/10asians.html |newspaper=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]] |date=2008-06-10 |access-date=2012-02-09 |archive-date=2021-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211112053151/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/06/10/education/10asians.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.modelminority.com/joomla/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=230:asian-americans-under-the-model-minority-gaze-&catid=36:coolies&Itemid=56 |title=Asian Americans Under the Model Minority Gaze |author=Tojo Thatchenkery |date=2000-03-31 |work=International Association of Business Disciplines National Conference |publisher=modelminority.com |access-date=2012-02-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318003048/http://www.modelminority.com/joomla/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=230:asian-americans-under-the-model-minority-gaze-&catid=36:coolies&Itemid=56 |archive-date=2012-03-18 |url-status=dead }}</ref>，也被稱為「{{link-en|永遠的外國人|perpetual foreigner}}」。<ref>{{cite book |title=The politics of Asian Americans: diversity and community |last=Lien |first=Pei-te |author2=Mary Margaret Conway |author2-link=Mary Margaret Conway |author3=Janelle Wong |year=2004 |publisher=Psychology Press |isbn=978-0-415-93465-7 |page=7 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o7ucGq1RZ-EC&q=%22asian%20americans%22%20perpetual%20foreigners&pg=PA7 |access-date=2012-02-09 |quote=In addition, because of their perceived racial difference, rapid and continuous immigration from Asia, and on going detente with communist regimes in Asia, Asian Americans are construed as "perpetual foreigners" who cannot or will not adapt to the language, customs, religions, and politics of the American mainstream. |archive-date=2021-03-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210326122542/https://books.google.com/books?id=o7ucGq1RZ-EC&q=%22asian+americans%22+perpetual+foreigners&pg=PA7 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Yellow: race in America beyond black and white |last=Wu |first=Frank H. |author-link=Frank H. Wu |year=2003 |publisher=[[Basic_Books|Basic Books]] |isbn=978-0-465-00640-3 |page=[https://archive.org/details/yellow00fran/page/79 79] |url=https://archive.org/details/yellow00fran  |quote=asian americans perpetual foreigners. |access-date=2012-02-09}}</ref>

